
# ðŸ“Œ DATA STRUCTURES â€“ ONE-PAGE ERROR HANDLING CHEAT SHEET



## ðŸ”´ UNIVERSAL (APPLIES TO ALL DS)

### Memory Allocation

```c
ptr = malloc(...);
if(ptr == NULL)  // ALWAYS
```

### NULL Dereference

```c
if(ptr == NULL) return;
```

### Free Rule

* Every `malloc()` â†’ exactly **one** `free()`
* Never use pointer after `free()`

---

## ðŸŸ¦ LINKED LIST

### Empty List

```c
if(head == NULL)
```

### Insert

| Case             | Check                           |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------- |
| Insert beginning | none                            |
| Insert end       | if head == NULL                 |
| Insert at pos    | pos <= 0 or traversal hits NULL |

### Delete

| Case       | Check             |
| ---------- | ----------------- |
| Empty list | head == NULL      |
| First node | update head       |
| Last node  | prev->next = NULL |
| Position   | pos > length      |
| Value      | not found         |

### Traversal

```c
while(temp != NULL)
```

### Head Update (MOST IMPORTANT)

Required when:

* insert first
* delete first
* reverse list

---

## ðŸŸ© STACK

### Overflow

| Type        | Check          |
| ----------- | -------------- |
| Array       | top == size-1  |
| Linked List | malloc == NULL |

### Underflow

```c
if(top == NULL)
```

### pop()

* Update top **before** free
* Must return value

### peek()

* Never modify stack

---

## ðŸŸ¨ QUEUE

### Overflow

| Type     | Check                  |
| -------- | ---------------------- |
| Array    | rear == size-1         |
| Circular | (rear+1)%size == front |

### Underflow

```c
if(front == NULL)
```

### Last Element Removed

```c
front = rear = NULL;
```

---

## ðŸŸª ARRAY

### Bounds

```c
if(index < 0 || index >= size)
```

### Insert

```c
if(count == capacity)
```

### Delete

```c
if(count == 0)
```

---

## ðŸŸ¥ TREE

### Root Check

```c
if(root == NULL) return;
```

### Recursive Base Case

ALWAYS handle NULL first.

### Delete Node

* Leaf
* One child
* Two children

---

## ðŸŸ« GRAPH

### Vertex Validation

```c
if(v < 0 || v >= V)
```

### Traversal

* Initialize visited array
* Prevent infinite loops

---

## ðŸ”¥ EXAM GOLDEN CASES (CHECK THESE EVERY TIME)

âœ” Empty structure
âœ” Single element
âœ” First node
âœ” Last node
âœ” Out-of-range index
âœ” Memory allocation failure

If you miss **any one** â†’ solution is incomplete.

---

## ðŸ’€ MOST COMMON EXAM FAIL MISTAKES

âŒ Using `=` instead of `==`
âŒ Returning pointer as `int`
âŒ Forgetting to update head/top/front
âŒ Freeing wrong node
âŒ No empty check before delete/pop

---

## FINAL BRUTAL TRUTH

Top students donâ€™t â€œrememberâ€ error handling.
They **pattern-match automatically**.

Before coding, ask yourself:

> empty?
> full?
> null?
> first?
> last?
